com.github.katjahahn.sections.idata

Class LookupTableEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.katjahahn.sections.idata.LookupTableEntry
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NameEntry, NullEntry, OrdinalEntry

    public abstract class LookupTableEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a lookup table entry. Every lookup table entry is either an ordinal entry, a name entry or a null entry. The null entry indicates the end of the lookup table.

      • apply

        public static LookupTableEntry apply(byte[] idatabytes,
                     int offset,
                     int entrySize,
                     long virtualAddress,
                     int importTableOffset)
        Creates a lookup table entry based on the given import table bytes, the size of the entry, the offset of the entry and the virtual address of the import section

        Parameters:
        idatabytes - the bytes of the import section
        offset - the offset of the entry (relative to the offset of the import section)
        entrySize - the size of one entry (dependend on the magic number)
        virtualAddress - of the import section (used to calculate offsets for given rva's of hint name entries)
        Returns:
        lookup table entry
